What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Panthenol Market?

Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Panthenol Market

The panthenol market is expected to witness market growth at a rate of 4.4% in the forecast period of 2022 to 2029 and is expected to reach USD 0.14 billion by 2029. Data Bridge Market Research report on panthenol market provides analysis and insights regarding the various factors expected to be prevalent throughout the forecast period while providing their impacts on the market's growth. The rise in the utilization of panthenol for manufacturing pharmaceuticals due to its properties like anti-inflammatory, wound healing, skin barrier repair is escalating the growth of panthenol market.

Panthenol is referred to as a pantothenic acid chemical substance, which is also called as vitamin B5. It occurs organically and can also be created from plant and animal sources. Panthenol is broadly used as a moisturizer in cosmetics and personal care products. Panthenol is a forerunner to vitamin B5 and can be utilized to combat vitamin B5 deficiency. A substantial number of the population lacks adequate vitamins and nutrients to support their body's functioning.

Major factors that are expected to boost the growth of the panthenol market in the forecast period are increase in the need for panthenol in different food products that are needed to create B5 additions and the growing in processed food business and feed products for animals. Furthermore, the rise in the health and wellness awareness population is further anticipated to propel the growth of the panthenol market. Moreover, the rising nutrient deficiency among the population and increase in the concern regarding animal welfare and nutrition is further estimated to cushion the growth of the panthenol market. On the other hand, the environmental concerns regarding the usage and production of panthenol is further projected to impede the growth of the panthenol market in the timeline period.

In addition, the growing usage of panthenol in the cosmetic industry for the manufacture of products such as mascara, foundation, lipsticks, and other formulations will further provide potential opportunities for the growth of the panthenol market in the coming years. However, the variation in the raw material prices might further challenge the growth of the panthenol market in the near future.

